    <question xml:id="ques-twos3">
      <title>Our Final Calculation</title>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Add up the appropriate multiples of <m>23</m> to calculate <m>12 \times 23</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          From<xref ref="table23arrows"/>, we see the entries in rows corredsponding to <m>2^2</m> 
          and <m>2^3</m> are <m>92</m> and <m>184</m>. So we conclude that <m>12 \times 23  = 92 + 184 = 276</m>.
        </p>
      </solution>
      
      
      
